Police have issued a CCTV image as part of an appeal for information after a Barclays bank branch was covered in red paint and had windows smashed as part of protest by a pro-Palestine group.Avon and Somerset Police said there are four people they want to speak to about the damage to the building in Bristol city centre on 10 June at about 03:00 BST.The building was one of a number targeted across England and Scotland by Palestine Action. Officers are appealing for anyone who knows who the four people are to contact them.
Police said they were looking for three men of slim build. All three were wearing black and had face coverings.There was also a woman of slim build who was wearing all black and was carrying a blue shopping bag.
